The paper discusses security and privacy issues in the IoT domain and proposes the use of Machine Learning (ML) algorithms and Blockchain (BC) techniques as countermeasures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the classification of literature based on ML algorithms and BC techniques, which indicates that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of ML algorithms also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper discusses cyber threats and vulnerabilities, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Science Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of IoT devices, which suggests that it may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
